gw.api.admin

Class TreeGroupInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.admin.TreeGroupInfo
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DashboardTreeGroupInfo

    public class TreeGroupInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    Used to represent a node in the tree view that displays groups and users on the team pages. This class is necessary because most nodes in the tree correspond to a single group but in one special case we need a node that represents a "pseudo group" (usually called "My Groups") which contains all the groups supervised or managed by the current user. This class provides a consistent interface for both a normal group and the special "My Groups" case.

      • TreeGroupInfo

        protected TreeGroupInfo()

      • TreeGroupInfo

        public TreeGroupInfo(Group group)
        Create the group info for the given group. If the group is null then return either the group information for the root group or the group information for the special pseudo group "my groups", depending on whether the current user has permission to view the root group.
        Parameters:
        group - the group to view or null to get a view of the "root" group (either the actual root group or "My Groups", depending on the user)
